<paragraph id="E97036DD3F74FFE3FF76FEC6FD01FEBB" blockId="65.[151,1437,320,923]" box="[151,737,320,347]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
Size. Known adult size reaching 
<quantity id="2E379B383F74FFE3FDE9FEC6FDB4FEBA" box="[520,596,320,347]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" unit="cm" value="6.5">6.5 cm</quantity>
total length.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A1D565563F74FFE3FF26FEE2FB18FC7A" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" type="description">
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F74FFE3FF26FEE2FA65FDEF" blockId="65.[151,1437,320,923]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
Morphology. D VI + I,14; A I,13; P 18–19. Moderately long body and distinctly large eyes. Snout short (shorter than eye diameter), with moderately steep and rounded profile. Caudal peduncle deep, but lower than body depth. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F74FFE3FF76FE2AFD92FE0B" bold="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">First dorsal fin higher than second dorsal fin (maybe in mature males only), third spine longest and elongate, interspinous membranes deeply incised.</emphasis>
No free pectoral-fin rays detected. Caudal fin rounded. Scales visible on dead specimens from reticulate pattern of pigmentation along scale edges, visibility on live specimens unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F74FFE3FF26FD9EFA9DFD06" blockId="65.[151,1437,320,923]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
Freshly dead coloration. Background coloration orange-beige, dark-brown or whitish, with orange markings dorsally, and 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F74FFE3FECDFDBBFCF4FDB6" bold="true" box="[300,788,572,599]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">7 rectangular, orange midlateral blotches</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F74FFE3FCC2FDBAFC97FDB6" box="[803,887,572,599]" captionStart="FIGURE 59" captionStartId="65.[151,250,1315,1339]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,946,1291]" captionTargetId="figure-329@65.[152,1436,946,1291]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURE 59. Freshly dead coloration of Gobius xoriguer. Photo by S. Iglésias, off eastern Corsica, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601749" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601749/files/figure.png" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
). Eyes with stripes radiating from the pupil to the orbital rim, including a broad horizontal stripe across the eye. One indistinct orange preorbital bar. Lips unmarked. 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F74FFE3FF76FD02FA7DFD7E" bold="true" box="[151,1437,644,671]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Cheek and opercle orange, possibly smoked gray in some individuals, with numerous rounded white spots</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="71F42A583F74FFE3FF41FD2EFF13FD22" box="[160,243,680,707]" captionStart="FIGURE 59" captionStartId="65.[151,250,1315,1339]" captionTargetBox="[152,1436,946,1291]" captionTargetId="figure-329@65.[152,1436,946,1291]" captionTargetPageId="65" captionText="FIGURE 59. Freshly dead coloration of Gobius xoriguer. Photo by S. Iglésias, off eastern Corsica, Southern France." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6601749" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6601749/files/figure.png" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
). On the anterior half of the first dorsal fin, an oblique, smokey gray blotch extending from the distal half of first spine to the base of fourth or fifth. Upper base of pectoral fins with an orange blotch (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F74FFE3FB6AFD4AFA91FD06" author="Iglesias, S. P. &amp; Vukic, J. &amp; Sellos, D. Y. &amp; Soukupova, T. &amp; Sanda, R." box="[1163,1393,716,743]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="445 - 449" refId="ref56737" refString="Iglesias, S. P., Vukic, J., Sellos, D. Y., Soukupova, T. &amp; Sanda, R. (2021 a) Gobius xoriguer, a new offshore Mediterranean goby (Gobiidae), and phylogenetic relationships within the genus Gobius. Ichthyological Research, 68 (3), 445 - 449. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10228 - 020 - 00797 - 9" type="journal article" year="2021">
Iglésias 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F74FFE3FB08FD4BFAFAFD07" box="[1257,1306,716,742]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">et al</emphasis>
. 2021a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F74FFE3FF26FD76FBCBFCEA" blockId="65.[151,1437,320,923]" box="[199,1067,752,779]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
