</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F74FFE3FF26FC92FD3BFCB2" blockId="65.[151,1437,320,923]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
Habitat. Circalittoral species, recorded from deep coralline beds composed of fixed or unattached red algae, between 62 and 
<quantity id="2E379B383F74FFE3FEAFFCBFFE75FCB2" box="[334,405,825,851]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.02" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" unit="m" value="102.0">102 m</quantity>
depth (
<bibRefCitation id="8D5E4B2C3F74FFE3FE08FCBEFD2FFCB2" author="Iglesias, S. P. &amp; Vukic, J. &amp; Sellos, D. Y. &amp; Soukupova, T. &amp; Sanda, R." box="[489,719,824,851]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66" pagination="445 - 449" refId="ref56737" refString="Iglesias, S. P., Vukic, J., Sellos, D. Y., Soukupova, T. &amp; Sanda, R. (2021 a) Gobius xoriguer, a new offshore Mediterranean goby (Gobiidae), and phylogenetic relationships within the genus Gobius. Ichthyological Research, 68 (3), 445 - 449. https: // doi. org / 10.1007 / s 10228 - 020 - 00797 - 9" type="journal article" year="2021">
Iglésias 
<emphasis id="DBBBEACF3F74FFE3FDA6FCBFFD98FCB3" box="[583,632,824,850]" italics="true" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">et al</emphasis>
. 2021a
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E97036DD3F74FFE3FF26FCDAFB18FC7A" blockId="65.[151,1437,320,923]" pageId="65" pageNumber="66">
